<h2>bibliometrix: Comprehensive Science Mapping Analysis</h2>
<p>Tool for quantitative research in scientometrics and bibliometrics.
    It provides various routines for importing bibliographic data from 'SCOPUS' (&lt;<a href="https://scopus.com">https://scopus.com</a>&gt;),
    'Clarivate Analytics Web of Science' (&lt;<a href="https://www.webofknowledge.com/">https://www.webofknowledge.com/</a>&gt;), 'Digital Science Dimensions' 
	(&lt;<a href="https://www.dimensions.ai/">https://www.dimensions.ai/</a>&gt;), 'Cochrane Library' (&lt;<a href="https://www.cochranelibrary.com/">https://www.cochranelibrary.com/</a>&gt;) 
	and 'PubMed' (&lt;<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/">https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/</a>&gt;) databases, performing bibliometric analysis 
    and building networks for co-citation, coupling, scientific collaboration and co-word analysis.</p>
